<h1><%= title_for(BootstrapLesson, 1, 3) %></h1>

<p>
  Now that we've got bootstrap set up, let's see what we can do with it.
</p>

<p>
  Let's go to the bootstrap website (quickly search "bootstrap" in your web browser) and let's click on "Components". We see a bunch of cool icons, we see some navbars, we see a bunch of cool stuff that we can use in our websites. This is looking awesome. Let's begin by adding a navbar to our site.
</p>

<p>
  If we click on "Navbar" on the navigation bar on the right hand side of the bootstrap website, it will take you to a section that explains how to implement the navbar. Let's scroll down and copy the bunch of code in the first example they give us. It should look something like this:
</p>

