<p>
  Let's go ahead and paste this into our <code>body</code> section of our HTML. Hop back into your browser and refresh the page, and boom, you see a navbar implemented just like that. Super awesome!
</p>

<p>
  Since we don't need the search bar or those dropdown menus, let's just delete that from the navbar. Let's delete everything from <code>&lt;ul class="nav navbar-nav"&gt;</code> to <code>&lt;/form&gt;</code>. Go back to our browser and refresh the page and now you should see a simpler looking navbar.
</p>

<%= image_tag 'simplebootstrapnav.png', class: 'screenshot' %>

<p>
